am.com/topic/220330-kerbals-drift-when-on-a-ladder-of-a-craft-that-is-accelerating/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it\u0027s not exactly it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI saw this actually, and was unsure. I feel it maybe has the same root cause, but this referred to it happening under acceleration yeah. Time warping when not thrust is being applied also causes this same behaviour. Feel free to merge though!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Navoan","CreatedById":133765,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-03-12T13:04:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/228085-spicat/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022228085\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/228085-spicat/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Spicat\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Just fyi, I think perhaps you changed this to incorrectly show v0.1.5 (as in the your quoted bug report), but my bug report is for v0.2.1\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Qs144Cp.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002210.09\u0022 height=\u002265\u0022 width=\u0022644\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Qs144Cp.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-03-12T13:17:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224371922\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224075\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221710248662\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133765\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Navoan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Navoan sai